  %ul
    %li A PHP script that makes a configurable directory tree available for file browsing, downloading and uploading. Supports an exclusion list for files and directories, as well as ftpd-style per-directory banners.
    %li A PHP script that reads entries from static text files in a directory and presents them in a simple blog-type interface. The most interesting feature of this script was a simple HTML parser I wrote which allowed me to use a custom markup tag to insert footnotes in the flow of the main text, which the script would then place at the bottom of the page.
    %li An idented sever implemented entirely in pure bourne shell (without bash extensions) using Dan Bernstein's tcptools.
    %li A custom init system for Linux intended to completely replace sysvinit. The idea was to have a centralized method for handling system services, which were defined in a single config file and interfaced with using a single shell command that provided access to all of the standard daemon function (start/stop/restart/reload/status).

